question: Olivia has 4 jars of chocolate chips in her pantry. Each jar of chocolate chips can decorate 14 brownies. Olivia wants to bake enough brownies to use up all of her chocolate chips. If each baking sheet holds 7 brownies, how many baking sheets worth of brownies should she bake?
answer:
She has enough chocolate chips for 4 * 14 = <<4*14=56>>56 brownies.
She needs 56 / 7 = <<56/7=8>>8 baking sheets to bake all of the brownies.
#### 8
